ubuntu-advantage-tools (19.5) UNRELEASED; urgency=medium

  * New upstream release (LP: #1832757):
    - cc: add a warning about download size before install
    - repo: un-comment ESM sources.list lines on repo disable
    - attach: two-factor auth reprompt only two-factor auth on failed 2fa
    - keyrings: regenerate keyrings on a trusty host
    - refresh keyrings to match current production for
      fips, fips-updates, cc-eal
    - apt: write commented -updates lines instead of omitting them
    - environ: allow lowercase ua_<config_option> overrides
    - logs: no longer redact secrets as logfile is root read-only
    - config: allow contract_url and sso_auth_url to have a trailing slash
    - apt: enable -updates if -updates from the Ubuntu archive is enabled
    - fips: display as pending when linux-fips is not the running kernel
    - status: redact technical support and expiry for free contracts
    - esm: on upgrade do not install preferences to pin never if esm enabled
    - esm: use Pin-Priority never apt preference file to disable esm initially
    - packaging: trusty should remove v1 esm key if present after upgrade
    - cli: check for root before checking for attach in assert_attached_root
    - apt: retry apt install and update commands 3 times simple backoff
    - apt-hook: Add basic i18n (good enough for lang packs)
    - status: emit a SERVICE header in status output
    - cc: update cc to cc-eal in docs, parameters and commandline help
    - docker: fix persisting generated uuid on images without machine-id files
    - status: unentitled services will report n/a
    - console log: remove level from messages
    - fips: only install/upgrade optional packages that are already on the
      system
    - esm and livepatch auto enabled on attach
    - don't attempt to disable inapplicable entitlements during detach
    - attach: suppress messages from inapplicable default entitlements
    - all repo entitlements now call apt-get update on enable
    - esm: add esm-v2 gpg keyring, drop old keyring, ignore aptKey directive
    - logs: separate console log devel from logfile level
    - honour enableByDefault obligations from contract server
    - d/postinst: Remove the old CACHE_DIR in postinst
    - d/postinst: adjust logfile permissions
    - d/control: depend on libapt-pkg<ABI_VERSION> to use pin-priority never
    - d/postrm: remove the ESM pinning file on purge
    - d/postrm: remove log files on package purge
    - d/postinst: remove public files and generate status cache on upgrade
    - esm: remove only the apt auth entry on disable, leaving sources.list
    - refresh: add subcommand to refresh all contract details
    - status: add --json cli formatting option
    - updated manpage and help docs

 -- Andreas Hasenack <andreas@canonical.com>  Mon, 15 Apr 2019 10:38:35 -0300

